race.description: Warburton Estate Agents Country Boosted Mdn Plate
race.comment: SHENANDOAH RIVER (7) stepped up in trip to 1100m last time at this track and ran below her best when seventh. Kept fresh since and she gets a better set-up with the drop in weight. HARAS (6) produced a nice effort on debut in better company last start over 1000m at this track when third. Promising type with improvement to come and shouldn't be a maiden for long. Has the speed to overcome the wide draw. CHAPPOLICIOUS (4) was in the firing line on the corner and finished third last time over 1000m at Dubbo when resuming from a spell. Roper keeps the ride from the inside gate and gets her chance. TIPSY MISS (8) Ole Kirk filly from an All Too Hard mare making her first appearance for the Ramsey stable. Finished fifth in a recent Scone trial over 900m. Place claims look best.
